version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2025-03-01"
abstract: >
  NormTrace is a structured methodological tool for assessing domestic normative alignment
  with international legal instruments. The current pilot focuses on disability rights
  in Mexico, using an initial contrast between the Convention on the Rights of Persons
  with Disabilities (CRPD) and domestic legislation.
repository-code: "https://github.com/Adelasantos12/NormTrace"
license: "MIT"
keywords:
  - legal analysis
  - normative alignment
  - conventionality control
  - disability rights
  - Mexico
  - international law
  - human rights
